## 1. Use Cleanup with useEffect

The most important pattern is ensuring your cleanup functions run properly:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  let isMounted = true;

  const fetchData = async () => {
    try {
      const response = await api.getData();
      // Only update state if component is still mounted
      if (isMounted) {
        setData(response);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      if (isMounted) {
        setError(error);
      }
    }
  };

  fetchData();

  // Cleanup function
  return () => {
    isMounted = false;
  };
}, []);
```

## 2. Use AbortController for Network Requests

For fetch requests, AbortController provides better cancellation:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  const abortController = new AbortController();

  const fetchData = async () => {
